Key Match Events: The New York Knicks defeated the Milwaukee Bucks 116-94.
Karl-Anthony Towns led the Knicks with 32 points.
Giannis Antetokounmpo finished with 24 points and 12 rebounds.
Damian Lillard had 19 points but missed all four of his three-point attempts.
Post-Match Reflections: Giannis Antetokounmpo expressed frustration with the Bucks' effort, stating the team didn't compete.
Antetokounmpo highlighted the importance of competing to have a chance to win.
Antetokounmpo mentioned the upcoming game against the Boston Celtics and the need to compete to avoid another loss.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bucks were playing the second night of a back-to-back after defeating the Utah Jazz.
Khris Middleton remains out indefinitely after offseason surgery on both ankles.
